76561197978273221,Not Recommended,292180,29641051,Posted: 1 February,all,Treklife,"Longtime FSX user and wanted to upgrade to a more recent flightsim. Thought I would try X-Plane out. Picked it up on a steam sale and was blown away with the land and water textures. Flying at night is so awesome in X-Plane.I noticed some things that really disappointed me.I was let down by the selection of aircraft packed in with the sim. Some are unfinished with no VC or cockpit. Also the default aircraft all have a tendency to roll to the left. I've tried calibrating my joystick, adjusting the settings in the sim. Nothing, I can't get the Cessna 172 to not roll to the left. And yes, I'm a private pilot. I know all about the left turning tendency, torque and MORE RIGHT PEDAL. I got all that from my CFI. But try and fly that sucker straight and level in X-Plane. Let go of the yoke and left turn...every time. That's an immersion breaker. Unless you turn on the auto pilot.Adjusting the controls is a nightmare. You have to set up control schemes for each aircraft. Why? Flaps, gear, lights and views should not change depending on what airplane I happen to be flying in.The ATC.... SO BAD. Disappointed by the primitive ATC in this game. Trying to fly IFR with the ATC is impossible in this sim. Just don't even use the ATC. Your ears will thank you.Lack of freeware aircraft. The selection of freeware is disappointing considering this is the tenth version of this game. And the payware seems to be very pricey with sales few and far between.Your local airfield will probably not have any buildings or hangars. Why? This is 2017. This is unacceptable in a flight sim that is active and still receiving updates in 2017. This breaks immersion and makes me feel like I have an incomplete product.Im sure there are people who say, ""Just download this AddOn to fix the ATC"", or ""You can download a program to re-create your airfield"". Why? Why should I have jump through all those hoops and spend time fixing a game that was sold to me as a complete product?I really want to like this sim. When I fire it up I find I'm fighting it more than enjoying it. Anybody else feel the same? Anybody have any suggestions?"
,Recommended,292180,13772598,"Posted: 1 January, 2015",all,Sp4wN7,Warning to the average Steam player . . . This is not a game . . . It is a simulation. I do not recommend for the jump in and go type. I like this game alot for its simulation value. X-Plane has a very advanced engine for aircraft simulation and for someone who likes realism . . . this is the air sim for you. If you like checklists prior to taking off . . . this is the game for you. If you like to jump in and go with no thought then don't waste your time with this sim. On the other hand if you want to learn how to fly a plane well enough to consider getting your PPL then download this gem and start learning!
,Recommended,292180,19683116,"Posted: 13 December, 2015",all,barbarbaron,"Pros:-> Good and accurate flight model for a desktop simulator.-> Visual capabilities are much more advanced than other desktop simulators.-> Informative for simulator hobbyists, hobbyist pilots and students.-> Navigation system (radio signals, gps simulators, autopilots) work good and feel close to the real thing.-> Keybinding system is very easy to configure and well thought.Cons:-> Sound system and stock aircraft audio effects are mediocre and sometimes annoying (repetitive sounds, cracks and pops). There are plugins that enhance the audio of x-plane but why should the user be forced to buy them?-> Stock aircraft contain unfinished and lackluster aircraft. The buyer expects all stock aircraft to be in excellent condition.-> User interface is somewhat unfriendly and there are no built-in tutorials for beginners.-> The advanced flight model which makes this simulator stand out among others, also needs a powerful system to be simulated perfectly. The flight model is tied to the framerates of rendering and when the simulation time is accelerated autopilot may function wrongly which makes accelerated intercontinental flights dangerous."
