76561198115733138,Recommended,292180,30580664,Posted: 17 March,all,mah_0003,"As you can probably see from my playtime, I really love this game. It is my most played game on steam and for good reason. I think I should first address the title ""game"". It really isn't a game at all, it's a simulation. A really darn complex simulation. Think of paying for the simulation engine, not for a fully featured title. The default aircraft aren't amazing, and only a few thousand (only :P) have 3D scenery. There is a wealth of free aircraft and scenery avaliable at theX-Plane.ORGforums and theX-Plane.ORGStore (X-Plane StoreandX-Plane Forums), probably the most generous community I've ever seen for a game. But if you want a detailed simulation, be prepared to pay money, this isn't a cheap hobby. I've probably spent well over $1000AUD on addons, hardware and software, as well as all of the free utilities and things that would usually come at a premium at a P3D or FSX forum. I would personally recommend against getting X-Plane 10 from steam, and instead get X-Plane 11 from Laminar's website, as X-Plane 10 is included free with it. The addons on steam are good quality, but you can often find them on sale at theX-Plane.ORGstore.The actual engine in X-Plane is fantastic. I can't really compare it to real life as I've never flown in real life, but certainly compared to FSX it's a huge improvement. You can really feel the air under your wings, as appossed to the ""flying on rails"" feel you get with FSX and P3D. The only real downside to X-Plane 10 is that it can only use a few of your cores, due to limitations with the OpenGL engine. This can lead to low framerates when you're using several high-fidelity aircarft and custom scenery. Even still, low framerates is far superior to random CTD's you get with FSX and P3D due to memory limitations.TL;DR:This is not a game. It's a simulation. Expect to have to pay big money for extreme-fidelity aircraft, but still less than P3D or FSX. It's a solid engine, runs well and consistantly. Have a high single-thread clock and a decent GPU if you want to get the best performance. The best addons are atX-Plane.ORGand not as DLC for this game, butDO NOT BUY X-Plane 10!Get X-Plane 11 from Laminar and you'll get X-Plane 10 included free! Highly recommend!"
