76561198052330390,Recommended,292180,20709385,"Posted: 23 January, 2016",all,Capt_Insano,"First, this is not a game it is a simulator.  Compared to FSX it has better flight dynamics.  I have over 10,000 hours in several multi-engine jet aircraft and it has the feel and reaction of the real thing.  FSX feels like driving a bus  compared to x-plane.  ATC is better in FSX and is okay for a simulator.  X-plane ATC is so bad I never use it.  I plan my routes to include descent and setting myself up for an approach without ATC because it is just unusable and doesn't even come close to the real thing.Scenery in x-plane is better for atmospheric conditions and the out of the box terrain is comparable to FSX out of the box.  FSX does have better add-on scenery available.  X-plane surpasses FSX on the actual runway.   X-plane runways follow the terrain and are very realistic.  FSX has better stock aircraft than x-plane so plan on adding a payware aircraft unless general aviation is your thing.If checklist are your thing, FSX add-on aircraft like PMDG 737NGX are probably better than many x-plane add-on aircraft from a switchology standpoint.  I have the PMDG 737NGX for FSX and the FJS 737-200 for x-plane.  Systems functionality is more realistic with the high end FSX add-ons, but x-plane add-ons are comparable and generally cheaper.  Cockpit graphics are better in FSX, but x-plane is catching up.  Weather conditions more accurately affect the aircraft in x-plane.  Try a 30 knot crosswing landing in FSX and x-plane and there is a noticable difference with x-plane being very realistic.It all depends on the desires of each simer.  If you are really into checklist procedures and in depth systems operations then get FSX and pay for a high end add-on like a PMDG aircraft.  If flight dynamics and a very realistic feel to the aircraft  that is close to the real deal then get x-plane.  I prefer x-plane and if it had a decent ATC I would probably uninstall FSX and exclusively go with x-plane.  I split time between the 2 right now.  Hope this helps anyone trying to make a decision."
