y, I was able to accomplish this part with slight stress, but I feel it would be almost impossible for the average person who is new to flight simulators.During flight, it is as if the game “forgets” some of my pre-programmed buttons and usually replaces it with something random. The “Lights” button becomes a “Pan-Left” button for example.At the end of the day, it is as if the game just does whatever it wants. I was en-route to an airport and I wanted to check the map (to see where I was). BEWARE OF MIS-CLICKS!! I clicked “global map” instead of “local map” and all of a sudden, I was in a different aircraft at some RANDOM airport. There is no warning message for things like this, but tons of warning messages for the scenery that you have to spontaneously know how to download as DLC vs. coming with the game as it should. The redeeming quality is that the DLC comes free with the game, YAY.I am still new to X-Plane, but I have been playing flight simulators for over 10 years, and I ""like"" this game, but feel VERY disappointed by it!"
