,Recommended,292180,17148369,"Posted: 20 July, 2015",all,Flashpan,"I don't normally write steam reviews, but this product has just blown me away! I have been flight siming for around  25 years and recently I have mostly been using Prepar3D. Prepar3D is a great product, but on my system it does not run smoothly (lots of stuttering) and the way it draws autogen one can see a visible pop-up boundary. These two issues really break emersion.Anyways I bought X-Plane 10 mainly out of curiosity. The first thing I noticed was how damn smooth it ran. For a laugh, I thought I'd max out the autogen stuff - trees, buildings and roads. I was expecting a slide-show, but what I got was a buttery smooth simulation.Given what was being rendered I couldn't believe my eyes!A lot of people complain about the scenery being generic. This may well be the case, but it is so well implemented that it just looks and feels 'real'. It's the details of how the buldings and trees are created with regard to the road network. They actually look integrated. Add to that urban traffic that looks very believable and a draw distance that doesn't show any pop up and a buttery smooth frame-rate, then one gets a very immersive simulation.With Prepar3d I know I'm in a sim because of all the issues I mentioned at the top of the post. But with X-Plane I really feel like I'm there. VFR flying in this sim is just a joy.Many complain about airport detail, but I have found no issues. I fly around the US Washington State area, where (so far) I have been able to download all the airports I need free of charge. As a bonus many of them look very good indeed.Is there anything I miss?Well yes. Lots of other air traffic and ATC, but I'm sure there are add ons out there that will address these two omissions!As a flight simmer, I can't recomend X-Plane enough. I wish I had moved over sooner!"
