76561198055586349,Recommended,292180,14666642,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,lennyQuick,"X-Plane : Right out of the box (as it were) the 64 bit version beats hands down in speed and looks FSX. FSX looks dated (it is) and needs a significant cost investment to bring the ground textures up to some reasonable level. Still, no matter your system  performance will suck if you intend to crank up the textures. And HUGE ISSUE whether with FSX or Prepar3D is OOMs. Yes, the dreaded out of memory errors. Say goodbye to that with X-Plane at 64 bit.Now first big minus in XPlane - NO SEASONAL TEXTURES!. Go ahead, fly in Canada in winter. Look - summer textures,lol. So you'll need to get a program for this huge deficiency.There is a growing body of payware for X-Plane and some fabulous planes such as the 777 and Flightfactor A350. Also the payware scenery, though nowhere near FSX/Prepar3D is starting to provide the necessary content to bring realism.UPDATE: Now updating my review. Giving thumbs up now because the first real attempt to provide a capable traffic AI - X-Life. The Deluxe version includes full ATC, flightplanning, follow-me car, etc. There is a growing body of airports which implements traffic AI through this program. Bravo. All of a sudden there is now a decent traffic program. Nowhere near Ultimate Traffic for P3D but well on its way.There is also another decent ATC proram called pilot2ATC which is for XPlane and P3D."
