76561198010241032,Recommended,292180,14016980,"Posted: 16 January, 2015",all,Jugganaut,"Alright, I've had XP 8, 9, and now 10. These are serious flight sims and not for kids expecting Ace Combat or an equivalent thereof where you can just load it and start fighting other aircraft, etc. I will break down the pros and cons:PRO:+More accurate flight models (i.e. I can finally do Pugachev's Cobra in my SU-35 without unrealistic altitude gain).+Can target all flying aircraft (for those days where shooting down an airliner gives you jollies).+Black smoke upon missle hits/Explosions for bombs.+Better graphics+Better supersonic modeling (much less computational flutter)+At full tilt, I can recognize my neighborhood (better world detail).+Wing flexing! (Finally)+Faster batch-converting for airfoils.Mixed:+/- Better AI for air combat but still no gun usage for OPFOR aircraft or complex manuevers. I know this isn't a combat sim but can someone make a plug-in for this? It'll be great for those bad days at the office when you just want to recreate a battle from the Korean War.CON:-Super complicated to get older aircraft up to the new version.-When you get older aircraft up to xp10, a huge amounts of adjustments needed in planemaker to get these aircraft flyable.-Air Traffic Control is junk, just worthless. Even if you set your comms right.-Requires extensive knowledge of previous XP versions to get any custom aircraft airworthy.-Only diehard flightsim fans will have the patience to figure out the complicated variables needed to fly this sim.-Generic modern-standard radar navigation systems, older aircraft can see like new ones without scan deflection restrictions and analogue vs digital system limitations.I love the X-plane series and I'm glad it is on Steam. It makes it easier than waiting for the store to carry the Full version than the boiled-down North American version. Hopefully fixes will be addressed in later patches.I recommend this only for diehard sim fans. Those expecting Ace Combat arcade action are going to be vastly disappointed."
